.TH JGREP 1 "2026" "The-JLC-Project" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
jgrep \- search for a pattern in files or stdin
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B jgrep
.I pattern
.RI [ file ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B jgrep
reads each
.I file
(or standard input if no files are given) line by line and prints every line
that contains
.IR pattern .
Pattern matching uses
.BR strstr (3)
(case-sensitive, literal string match).
This is a minimal JLC equivalent of
.BR grep (1).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
At least one match found.
.TP
.B 1
Wrong number of arguments.
.TP
.B 2
Cannot open a file.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Search for "error" in a log file:
.EX
jgrep error /var/log/syslog
.EE
.TP
Search stdin:
.EX
dmesg | jgrep usb
.EE
.TP
Search multiple files:
.EX
jgrep TODO *.c
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR grep (1),
.BR srt (1)
.SH AUTHORS
The-JLC-Project contributors.
